title: Darwin's Doubt and Intelligent Design - Collection 5
description:
Darwin's Doubt and Intelligent Design - Collection 5:

We have here 21 titles:

-  Barash - Homo Mysteries; Evolutionary Puzzles of Human Nature (2012)

-  Bergman - The Dark Side of Charles Darwin; a Critical Analysis of an Icon of Science (2011)

-  Botha & Knight (Eds.) - The Cradle of Language (2009)

-  Cracraft & Donoghue (Eds.) - Assembling the Tree of Life (2004)

-  Eddy & Knight (Eds.) - William Paley Natural Theology; or, Evidence of the Existence and Attributes of the Deity.. (2006)

-  Faulkner - Universe by Design; an Explanation of Cosmology and Creation (2004)

-  Gillen - Body by Design; Fearfully and Wonderfully Made (2001)

-  Hitching - The Neck of the Giraffe; Where Darwin Went Wrong (1982)

-  Johnson - Darwin on Trial, 3e (2010)

-  Kahn - Design of the Universe; the Heavens and the Earth (1954)

-  Klein - Survival of the Nicest; How Altruism Made Us Human and Why It Pays to Get Along (2014)

-  Lienesch - In the Beginning; Fundamentalism, the Scopes Trial, and the Making of the Antievolution Movement (2007)

-  Lynden-Bell et al (Eds.) - Water and Life; the Unique Properties of H2O (2010)

-  Marshall - The Atheist's Riddle; Language, Information, and the Case for Intelligent Evolution

-  Marshall - The Atheist's Riddle II; Evolution (2005)

-  Martin - How We Do It; the Evolution and Future of Human Reproduction (2013)

-  Parkyn - Human Design; Discover the Person You Were Born to Be (2009)

-  Restak - Mind; the Big Questions (2012)

-  Sherratt & Wilkinson - Big Questions in Ecology and Evolution (2009)

-  Suddendorf - The Gap; the Science of What Separates Us from Other Animals (2013)

-  Yahya - The Cambrian Evidence That Darwin Failed to Comprehend (2007)
